  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIn the stable futures upgrade the RPC handler has gotten unnecessarily complex. There is duplicate code and inbound state machine can be simplified. \r\n\r\nThis issue is an exercise in async/await and future handling. I imagine the easiest way to handle the excessive states in the inbound substream state-machine is to build an async function that handles the polling, sending and flushing of a substream. This would return a Future that resolves to the underlying substream. This way the substream state would only have a `busy` variant containing the future that resolves to the substream. \r\n",
